The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, April 15, 2004 				 Jerry Rao is Nasscom chairman
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, April 14: Nasscom, the apex association for the IT software and services industry, today appointed Jerry Rao as its chairman. Rao, who is chairman and CEO of MphasiS BFL, will lead the organisation during 2004-05. S. Ramadorai, CEO, TCS, will be the vice-chairman. 																								The task ahead for us at Nasscom continues to be challenging in the present challenging and dynamic environment. As the premier body, we will require to adopt a focused approach especially on issues like security and quality, Rao said.																								My endeavour will be to establish India as a high-quality, secure, reliable software powerhouse and centre for best practices in the BPO industry. We will continue to build on the global trade development program and pro-actively engage with think-tanks, policy makers and academicians, he added. 																								During this year, Nasscom will attempt to put in place a long-term vision for the industry and the association, beyond revenue targets to focus on multiple parameters of industrys value proposition with measurable indices to define them. 
